OL,3,CThe Jerseyman who wrote the first
OL,4,CJerriais-French Dictionary
OL,6,FFrancois says: "We spoke Jerriais all
OL,7,Fthe time, every day, all day, and I
OL,8,Fdidn't know any English.
OL,10,F"All the children were in the same
OL,11,Fboat from the country, so when we went
OL,12,Fto school we had to learn pretty darn
OL,13,Fquick, and we did."
OL,15,FDr Le Maistre not only catalogued
OL,16,Fwords but also recorded the richness
OL,17,Fof different pronunciations across the
OL,18,FIsland and highlighted analogies with
OL,19,Fwords in other Channel Islands and
OL,20,Fmainland Normandy.
