OL,3,CThe Jerseyman who wrote the first
OL,4,CJerriais-French Dictionary
OL,6,FHad it not been for Dr Le Maistre's
OL,7,Fdedication, many recorded words and
OL,8,Fexpressions could have been lost
OL,9,Fforever.
OL,11,FFrancois explains: "You have to take
OL,12,Fyour cap off and say well done because
OL,13,Fboy what he did was fantastic.
OL,15,F"We wouldn't have the Jerriais that we
OL,16,Fhave today if it had not been for my
OL,17,Ffather, so yes, I'm very proud."
