OL,3,CThe Jerseyman who wrote the first
OL,4,CJerriais-French Dictionary
OL,6,FDespite being surrounded by Jerriais
OL,7,Fspeakers Frank's grandson, Charlie Le
OL,8,FMaistre, only truly found his passion
OL,9,Ffor the language seven years ago.
OL,10,FHowever, he now wishes he learnt it
OL,11,Fsooner.
OL,13,FHe says: "It has really transformed my
OL,14,Funderstanding of my Grandfather, my
OL,15,FPoppa, and in some respects, I feel a
OL,16,Fbit disappointed with myself because
OL,17,Fif I had been able to speak the
OL,18,Flanguage, our relationship would have
OL,19,Fbeen completely different."
