OL,3,CThe Jerseyman who wrote the first
OL,4,CJerriais-French Dictionary
OL,6,FCharlie has certainly made up for lost
OL,7,Ftime. Now a teacher of Jerriais, like
OL,8,Fhis father, he and Francois hope they
OL,9,Fcan continue to keep the language
OL,10,Falive, along with Dr Frank's legacy.
OL,12,FCharlie concludes: "We are on a huge
OL,13,Fjourney to revitalise the language and
OL,14,Fyou know it is a huge undertaking and
OL,15,Fit's going to take a long long time
OL,16,Fbut his legacy is so important to our
OL,17,Flearners today.
