OL,3,CThe Jerseyman who wrote the first
OL,4,CJerriais-French Dictionary
OL,6,F"I think if my grandfather could see
OL,7,Fwhat was happening now, he really
OL,8,Fwould be pleasantly surprised and very
OL,9,Fvery encouraged."
OL,11,FThe Le Maistre family vows to preserve
OL,12,Fthe 652-page dictionary, not only for
OL,13,Fnew learners of the language, but to
OL,14,Fprotect their family legacy for many
OL,15,Fyears to come.
